&lt;p&gt;Clinical Specialist Paediatric Physiotherapist - Band 7&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Permanent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full Time (37.5)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;North Tees and Hartlepool NHS Foundation Trust have an exciting opportunity to join the Paediatric Physiotherapy Team. We are seeking an enthusiastic experienced physiotherapist to join our friendly and motivated team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is open to a Physiotherapist with at least 5 year’s Paediatric experience and extensive knowledge and management of complex neurodevelopmental conditions. You will need to be able to undertake the comprehensive specialist assessment of patients, including those with a complex presentation, using investigative and analytical skills, and to formulate individualised management and treatment plans, using clinical reasoning, and utilising a wide range of treatment skills and options to formulate a specialised programme of care. To plan, deliver and evaluate the physiotherapy intervention in partnership with health, education and social services colleagues; and together lead the delivery and evaluation of all elements of the programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The majority of this post will be to deliver therapy within specialist provision setting and to also provide support at home.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Leadership skills are preferred.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If interested in this post, please contact Caron Nicholson/Kendra Smith (01642 383105) for more information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameCaron Nicholson/Kendra SmithJob titleClinical Team Leader Paediatric Therapies/ Operational Lead Paedatric TherapiesTelephone number01642 383105&lt;/p&gt;
